  "prompt": "What causes anus cancer?",
  "response": "Several factors can contribute to the development of anal cancer:\n\n1. Human Papillomavirus (HPV) infection\n- Most common cause\n- High-risk HPV strains (especially types 16 and 18)\n- Can be transmitted through sexual contact\n\n2. Risk factors:\n- Multiple sexual partners\n- History of anal or genital warts\n- Weakened immune system\n- HIV/AIDS\n- Smoking\n- Advanced age\n\n3. Additional risk factors:\n- Receptive anal sex\n- Chronic inflammation of the anal area\n- Prior history of cervical, vulvar, or vaginal cancer\n- Family history of cancer\n\n4. Other potential contributors:\n- Certain sexual practices\n- Lack of HPV vaccination\n- Poor immune system function\n\n5. Prevention methods:\n- HPV vaccination\n- Safe sexual practices\n- Regular screening\n- Avoiding smoking\n- Maintaining a healthy immune system\n\nWhile these factors increase risk, not everyone with these characteristics will develop anal cancer. Regular medical check-ups and screenings are recommended for early detection and prevention.",
